<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFA16A1EFF479A9F16E8B9ED" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFA16A1EFF479A9F16E8B9ED" blockId="90.[185,1392,3230,3471]" lastBlockId="90.[1454,2667,702,2985]" pageId="90" pageNumber="848">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFF479A9F1FBAB7D5" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[187,442,3270,3303]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">Eptesicus anatolicus</taxonomicName>
was previously included as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFBEA9A9F1A83B7D5" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[1046,1155,3270,3303]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
, but genetic and morphological data suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFD7A9AB41D2DB63C" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[646,813,3309,3342]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
is a distinct species. According to genetic data presented byJ. Juste and colleagues in 2013,it is either sister to a clade including 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFF409B651F6EB66F" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[188,366,3388,3421]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pachyomus">E. pachyomus</taxonomicName>
, a paraphyletic 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFDAF9B651CE9B66F" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1774" box="[595,745,3388,3421]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="serotinus">E. serotinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFD079B651D74B66F" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[763,884,3388,3421]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC3B9B651A37B66F" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[967,1079,3388,3421]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
(using mitochondrial genes) or is in a clade with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFDC09B3A1CB3B6B6" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[572,691,3427,3460]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFD3E9B3A1D71B6B6" baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[706,881,3427,3460]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hottentotus">E. hottentotus</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EFC429B3A1A2CB6B6" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[958,1068,3427,3460]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
(using nuclear genes). Nevertheless, I. V. Artyushin and col leagues in 2018 found a similarly conflicting dataset that supported the traditional view that 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF76197DC170EBA90" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[2205,2318,389,418]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
includes both E. ogneuvi and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF7AF97F016FCBAF8" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[2131,2300,425,458]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
based on nuclear genes. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF7ED978D16E8BAC3" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[2065,2280,468,497]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">Eptesicus ognevi</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF6C2978D17EFBAC3" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[2366,2543,468,497]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">E. anatolicus</taxonomicName>
are 1ncluded as distinct species here, pending a more complete genetic and morphological study encompassing the full distributions of all taxa in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF6B2943717C0B9BD" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[2382,2496,622,655]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="bottae">E. bottae</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="EDD35797FFA16A1EF6379437145BB9BD" box="[2507,2651,622,655]" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF7EE94CD1712B987" authorityName="Felten" authorityYear="1971" box="[2066,2322,660,693]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="anatolicus">Eptesicus anatolicus</taxonomicName>
might be found sympatrically with 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFA16A1EF9A494E718CFB9ED" authorityName="Bobrinski" authorityYear="1918" box="[1624,1743,702,735]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Eptesicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="90" pageNumber="848" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ognevi">E. ognevi</taxonomicName>
in the southern Caucasus. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
